I have an OnDemand instance with Confluence. I'm using the default home page layout, I believe (with the recent activity on the right). I'm currently in Brazil. Last night Brazil jumped an hour ahead to summer (Daylight Saving) time. When I log in to Confluence, instead of "recent activity" I get the following error message:

{noformat}Error formatting macro: recently-updated-dashboard: org.joda.time.IllegalFieldValueException: Value 0 for hourOfDay is not supported: Illegal instant due to time zone offset transition: 2013-10-20T00:42:54.852 (America/Sao_Paulo){noformat}

You'll probably want to see the [Jota-Time documentation|http://joda-time.sourceforge.net/faq.html#illegalinstant] and [Stack Overflow|http://stackoverflow.com/questions/5451152/how-to-handle-jodatime-illegal-instant-due-to-time-zone-offset-transition]. Also see also your own [Confluence documentation|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CONFKB/Confluence+Dashboard+Fails+to+Display+Due+to+Incorrect+Timezone].

