The Health Check plugin will identify system plugins that are down, and fail the health check. In many cases these plugins are disabled in the database. For example:

{noformat}
confluence=# select * from bandana where bandanakey='plugin.manager.state.Map';
 bandanaid | bandanacontext |        bandanakey        |                                   bandanavalue                                    
-----------+----------------+--------------------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
         1 | _GLOBAL        | plugin.manager.state.Map | <map>
                                                       :   <entry>
                                                       :     <string>confluence.search.contentname</string>
                                                       :     <boolean>false</boolean>
                                                       :   </entry>
{noformat}

If the plugin is critical for Confluence, then the health check plugin should try and enable it to save the end user some effort. 

Alternatively, it should be impossible to disable these plugins, as they are critical for Confluence to function correctly.

